cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DL 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with recommender systems, which are widely used in information retrieval applications. The paper also proposes a deep learning method for cross-domain recommendation, which falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of latent representations and knowledge transfer also suggests a possible fit with the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the use of a Variational Autoencoder (VAE) model for handling sparse data and cold start scenarios suggests a possible fit with the Deep Learning (cs.DL) sub-category.
